<para id="para-00001">Glucose is the body’s primary short-term energy source. Its catabolism begins with <term id="term-00001">glycolysis</term>, a series of ten enzyme-catalyzed reactions that break down glucose into 2 equivalents of pyruvate, CH<sub>3</sub>COCO<sub>2</sub><sup>–</sup>. The steps of glycolysis, also called the <emphasis effect="italics">Embden–Meyerhoff pathway</emphasis> after its discoverers, are summarized in <link target-id="fig-00001"/>.</para>
