n to green phosphate ion. The separated enzyme product shows a cyclopentadiene tilted 90 degree right; its upper left position is bonded to encircled blue “Enz” whose bond is intersected by a pink spiral line; the tip shows an embedded blue nitrogen bonded to a blue hydrogen a blue nitrogen cation bonded to a green phosphorous double bonded to an oxygen on the left and bonded to two oxygen anions at the bottom. 2-phosphoglycerate shows a carbonyl group whose carbon is bonded to an oxygen anion on the right; the carbon of carbonyl group is bonded to CH2OH (pink OH) at the bottom (green); HCOPO3 to the power two minus (pink O and blue phosphate) intersects the previous bond.">
