<section id="sect-00008">
<title>Steps <span class="magenta-text">9</span>–<span class="magenta-text">10</span> of <link target-id="fig-00001"/>: Dehydration and Dephosphorylation</title>
<para id="para-00011">Like most <emphasis effect="italics">β</emphasis>-hydroxy carbonyl compounds, 2-phosphoglycerate undergoes a ready dehydration in <emphasis effect="bold"><span class="magenta-text">step 9</span></emphasis> by an E1cB mechanism (<link document="m00278"/>). The process is catalyzed by enolase, and the product is phosphoenolpyruvate, abbreviated PEP. Two Mg<sup>2+</sup> ions are associated with the 2-phosphoglycerate to neutralize the negative charges.</para>
